    "[36], which enhances LLM reasoning with tools and memory, taking sensory data x S as input and generating trajectories (waypoints) a Tw; ADAPT by Jin et al. [49], which trains a model for action narration and reasoning using vehicular navigation videos x Vn, generating action narrations a Na and reasoning explanations Er; DriveGPT4 by Xu et al.",
    "[50], an interpretable end-to-end autonomous driving system that takes videos x V, questions x Q, and control signals x Cs as inputs, and generates question answers a Aq and control signals a Cs; LLM-driver by Chen et al. [51], which integrates compact numeric vectors into LLMs, taking route x R, vehicle x Iv, and pedestrian information x Ip as inputs, and generating actions a A and interpretations a E; Graph VQA by Sima et al.",
    "[53], a novel framework for reasoning about a driving scene, taking figures x F as input and generating low-level control commands a C l.As research in this field progresses, we expect to see more advanced and unified frameworks that leverage the power of LLMs to achieve human-like decision-making and control in autonomous vehicles, addressing challenges such as reasoning, interpretability, and generalization.",
    "V. CONCLUSIONS AND FUTURE DIRECTIONSThis survey comprehensively reviewed the recent progress of integrating LLMs into the knowledge-based AD systems.",
